      "content": "Local community groups are often concerned about high-density zoning because they fear it will lead to gentrification and displacement of long-time residents. This can indeed increase the cost of living, making it unaffordable for lower-income families. Additionally, they worry that the character of existing neighborhoods will be lost, as new developments may not align with the historical or cultural identity of the area. To address these concerns, it's important to emphasize that high-density zoning can be implemented with thoughtful planning that includes affordable housing mandates, community benefits agreements, and design guidelines that respect the character of neighborhoods. By doing so, cities can create inclusive, diverse communities that benefit from economic growth while preserving the unique identity of each neighborhood.",
